{"tid":1780748,"cid":18,"subCid":0,"title":"Dead Poets Society 暴雨驕陽","createTime":"2019-12-12T15:18:07.000Z","updateTime":"2019-12-15T11:18:35.000Z","uid":331012,"like":15,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":14,"replies":[{"pid":"a6456ad35e2a50eba4f062e90ef76a30193cddce","tid":1780748,"uid":331012,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-12-12T15:18:07.000Z","msg":"有冇人中意尼套戲？<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 頭先穩左一次<br />\n發現尼套經典文學電影竟冇人開過post<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n我個人最中意既角色係Knox 佢好浪漫 我認為佢係少數學習到Keating既精神既學生<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/love.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n最經典之一應該係Keats同McAllister果段對話：<br />\nMcAllister: You take a big risk by encouraging them to be artists, John. When they realize they're not Rembrandts, Shakespeares or Mozarts, they'll hate you for it.<br />\nKeating: We're not talking artists, George, we're talking freethinkers.<br />\nMcAllister: Freethinkers at seventeen?<br />\nKeating: Funny &mdash; I never pegged you as a cynic.<br />\nMcAllister: Not a cynic, a realist. &quot;Show me the heart unfettered by foolish dreams, and I'll show you a happy man.&quot;<br />\nKeating: &quot;But only in their dreams can men be truly free. 'Twas always thus, and always thus will be.&quot;<br />\nMcAllister: Tennyson?<br />\nKeating: No, Keating.<br />\n<br />\n我比較認同McAllister既睇法 成日覺得諗住d無謂野，幼稚或者冇可能實現既野好浪漫時間，到頭黎都係一無所有，但尼個想法又好似太負面<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n同時，Keats既說話又錯唔晒。因為實現唔到，所以你成日幻想住佢，做到所謂<span style=\"color: red;\">in their dreams can men be truly free</span> . 因為，你係幻想既期間比左動力自己去實踐人地認為既「foolish dreams」 <br />\n<br />\n最後用John Lennon既寫既歌 Strawberry Fields Forever 既一個做結尾：<br />\n<em>Living is easy with eyes closed<br />\nMisunderstanding all you see</em><br />\n<br />\n希望有同好人出現！ 不喜勿插<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"24368b7f4c34f2447c9d5c4ffc1ad0c0619d6ae6","tid":1780748